''See also [[säd]]''
==English==

===Etymology===
Derived from Old English '''sæd''', literally meaning "sated", and later meaning "weary."

===Adjective===
'''sad''' ({{compar}}: '''[[sadder]]''', {{superl}}: '''[[saddest]]''')

# [[Unhappy]] <!--needs a better definition-->
# Suffering from depression.
# (of a song etc.) Moody, full of feeling.
# Pathetic, nerdy.

====Antonyms====
* [[happy]]

